EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Emergency Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the commissioner of emergency management to report on the citys preparedness and response to citywide public health emergencies
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the commissioner of emergency management to report on the citys preparedness and response to citywide public health emergencies.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to temporary space for outdoor non-tobacco hookah operation
EventItemMatterName: Temporary space for outdoor non-tobacco hookah operation.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, S.7628A/A.9657, an act to amend the public housing law, in relation to establishing the housing access voucher program.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing the housing access voucher program. (S.7628A/A.9657)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil and Human Rights
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring an exit interview for departing and retiring municipal employees
EventItemMatterName: Requiring an exit interview for departing and retiring municipal employees.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Resiliency and Waterfronts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to climate resiliency design guidelines and resiliency scoring
EventItemMatterName: Climate resiliency design guidelines and resiliency scoring.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to studying the feasibility of electrifying existing buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Studying the feasibility of electrifying existing buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on Congress to pass and the President to sign the Energy Innovation and Carbon Dividend Act of 2019 (H.R. 763).
EventItemMatterName: Energy Innovation and Carbon Dividend Act of 2019 (H.R. 763)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the police department to report on mental health support services for employees
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the police dept to report on mental health support services for employees.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to continuation of the New York city rent stabilization law of nineteen hundred sixty-nine
EventItemMatterName: Continuation of the NYC rent stabilization law of 1969.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon Congress to introduce and pass legislation to establish a National Bank for Infrastructure and Manufacturing, to help finance the estimated $4.6 trillion required to modernize and repair infrastructure in the United States.
EventItemMatterName: Establish a National Bank for Infrastructure and Manufacturing.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, A.6775/S.1253, to designating the county of Kings a cease and desist zone and establishing an affirmative defense to violations of nonsolicitation orders and cease and desist zones.
EventItemMatterName: Designating the county of Kings a cease and desist zone and establishing an affirmative defense to violations of nonsolicitation orders and cease and desist zones. (A.6775/S.1253)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Department of Environmental Conservation to establish indoor air quality standards and measure indoor air quality in New York City schools.
EventItemMatterName: Establish indoor air quality standards and measure indoor air quality in NYC schools.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign legislation that reforms New York States notary laws for new and renewing notary applicants.
EventItemMatterName: Reforms New York States notary laws for new and renewing notary applicants.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation adopting more stringent standards around corporations names that mimic government agencies to protect City residents from deed theft.
EventItemMatterName: Adopting more stringent standards around corporations names that mimic government agencies to protect City residents from deed theft.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation that increases the felony classification of crimes applicable to the prosecution of a fraudulent conveyance of residential real estate.
EventItemMatterName: Increases the felony classification of crimes applicable to the prosecution of a fraudulent conveyance of residential real estate.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign S.1203/A.1911, an act to amend the general business law, in relation to biometric privacy.
EventItemMatterName: Biometric Privacy (S.1203/A.1911)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget.
EventItemMatterName: Approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the police department to submit reports on enforcement of jaywalking
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the police department to submit reports on enforcement of jaywalking.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States Congress to pass, and the President  to sign, S.2689, sponsored by Senator Cory Booker, which would prohibit the use of biometric recognition technology and biometric analytics in certain federally assisted rental dwelling units, and for other purposes.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibit the use of biometric recognition technology and biometric analytics in certain federally assisted rental dwelling units, and for other purposes. (S.2689)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York Police Department to create a permanent, year-round harbor patrol in the Bronx, and review its allocation plan for citywide harbor patrols, in order to address concerns in the City Island area.
EventItemMatterName: NYPD to create a permanent, year-round harbor patrol in the Bronx, and review its allocation plan for citywide harbor patrols, in order to address concerns in the City Island area.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to accessibility in small businesses
EventItemMatterName: Accessibility in small businesses.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs and Business Licensing
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to authorizing the department of consumer and worker protection to issue temporary operating licenses to sidewalk caf applicants if certain requirements are satisfied
EventItemMatterName: Authorizing the department of consumer and worker protection to issue temporary operating licenses to sidewalk caf applicants if certain requirements are satisfied.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to reporting on moneys on deposit
EventItemMatterName: Reporting on moneys on deposit.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the reporting on non-depository city financial services.
EventItemMatterName: Reporting on non-depository city financial services.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign H.R. 5337, the Disaster Assistance Equity Act, which would amend the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act to provide assistance for common interest communities, condominiums and housing cooperatives damaged by a major storm.
EventItemMatterName: Disaster Assistance Equity Act (H.R. 5337)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring certain retail food stores to post notices on the food donation web portal concerning the availability of excess food, and arranging for the transportation and retrieval of such food
EventItemMatterName: Requiring certain retail food stores to post notices on the food donation web portal concerning the availability of excess food, and arranging for the transportation and retrieval of such food.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women and Gender Equity
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing rental assistance to survivors of domestic violence
EventItemMatterName: Providing rental assistance to survivors of domestic violence.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter and the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring sheriffs and city marshals to report housing displacement to the department of social services/human resources administration to evaluate eligibility for legal counsel
EventItemMatterName: Requiring sheriffs and city marshals to report housing displacement to the department of social services/human resources administration to evaluate eligibility for legal counsel.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to requiring the department of education to report on metrics regarding remote learning during the COVID-19 pandemic
EventItemMatterName: DOE to report on metrics regarding remote learning during the COVID-19 pandemic.
